{
  "texts": [
    "They operate within the environment of their firm and its customers, partners, and competitors.",
    "This environment might affect how effectively executives and TMTs can influence their firms, as noted by Hambrick (2007) in their extension of the basic mechanism of UET.",
    "The firm type characterizes typical configurations of different organizational resources in this environment.",
    "A segmentation of organizational resource configurations with the potential to affect AI adoption is the distinction between startup firms and incumbent firms (Kohler, 2016).",
    "Both types have different resources that might help TMTs utilize their AI literacy to establish AI orientation and HR-related AI implementation ability."
  ]
}